{
  "stem": "1826.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 211.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then she told-- and this doctor was mobilized by the Soviet right away, but not as a soldier, but as a doctor.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And all the men, you know, had to go there, and he had to say whether they are healthy or not healthy, you know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So they came to Maria Nikitschna to thank her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she said-- told them, I don't want anything from you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Only thing-- one thing-- I don't want [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Grisha-- ?] me-- to go to the army, because you could have been killed next day as a soldier, you know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then she-- he promised her, when I went to be examined, so he gave me some kind, like six weeks, you know-- like six weeks to get a little healthier, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then I didn't go to the army, because some of them, you know, I could-- I know two guys who got killed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So I didn't go to the army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But now it came out, I thought that I was the only Jew survivor, you know, of the 15000.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then I found out that there was one, also a Russian woman.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Her name was [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Sura ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Tarasova ?], who was rather of loose, shall we say, morals.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But she was hiding eight Jews in her basement.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Her basement.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "She was receiving-- she slept with the German officers to get food, but she-- the food was for this Jew-- for the Jewish guys who were there in the basement.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So I found out that I was not the only survivor, and we were there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And see, they-- they were a little naive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They went-- she went to the Soviet authorities and expected to get at least some help, you know, because food was scarce [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
